President Obama has announced the recipients of the National Medal of Science and the National Medal of Technology and Innovation. The National Medal of Science recognizes individuals who have made significant contributions to science and engineering. The recipients include researchers from various fields such as biology, chemistry, engineering, and mathematics. The National Medal of Technology and Innovation, on the other hand, honors individuals or companies that have made outstanding contributions to the promotion of technology for the betterment of the United States. The recipients will be awarded at a White House ceremony on October 7. President Obama praised the recipients for their achievements and their impact on the nation, both intellectually and economically.